WHO   — Conditioning · Hypnopaedia — desire, installed in your sleep
WHAT  — The installation of desire: slogans whispered thousands of times in childhood become unquestionable instinct.
WHERE — BNW · BRAVE NEW WORLD  Framework inputs: Brave New World (Aldous Huxley, 1932)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the deepest control is over what you want — engineer the wants and ‘freedom’ chooses exactly as designed.
HOW   — By electric shocks for infants, and recorded slogans played in sleep until they are felt as one's own thoughts.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I whisper ‘everyone belongs to everyone else’ ten thousand times while you sleep — and you wake believing it was always your own idea.

